. EXERCISE: What should Black do here to defend? --- ANSWER: He has a great
defence with} Rc8 $3 {when White can try:} 19. Rxd4 (19. gxh5 g5 {followed by ...Rc6 trapping White's queen! For example} 20. e6 Rc6 21. Rxd4 Rxe6 {and Black
wins}) 19... Ng7 20. Nc3 f5 {and although White managed to hold a draw in L.Aronian-P.Leko, Moscow 2006, I much prefer Black here.}) 15... Qb8 $1 {Now d7
is momentarily poisoned.} 16. Bh6 ({After both} 16. Qxd7 Rd8) ({and} 16. Rxd7
Bc8 {material is lost for the first player.}) 16... Re8 17. Nc3 Nxe5 {
Snatching a second pawn, which is risky but if the e5-pawn can be removed then
