Bxg2 19. Nxf7 ({Alternatively:} 19. Nxd7 Qb7 {keeps everything defended.}) (19.
Nxg6 hxg6 20. Kxg2 Qb7+ 21. Kg1 Nf6 22. Qc4 Rad8 23. Nd5 Nxd5 24. Rxd5 Bf6 {
is another example of Black keeping hold of the extra pawn and developing
