20. g4 $1 Bb7 21. Qd2 a6 22. a4 f5 23. Bxd6 Rxe3 24. Qxe3 Bxd6 25. Qh6 {
and suddenly Ng5 and threats of mate are in the air. The game finished} Be7 26.
gxf5 Nxf5 27. Bxf5 gxf5 28. Kh1 $1 Bf6 29. Rg1+ Kh8 30. Nh4 {1-0.}) ({b)} 5...
Be7 6. Nc3 d5 {is a solid line for Black if you don't like this Benoni type
structure. We have seen ...Be7 and ...d5 against Nb1-d2 lines, and Black
