g6 (7... d6 8. Nc3 g6 {might be a better move order, since 7...g6 allows some
tricks (which Black can deal with, I should point out). White continues} 9. Bf4
Bg7 {and now:} 10. Qa4+ {is one reason why ...d6 was delayed in the main game,
as this check can be awkward to meet. Then} (10. e4 Bxf1 11. Kxf1 O-O 12. h3
Re8 13. Re1 a6 14. a4 Ra7 15. g4 Rb7 16. Kg2 h5 17. g5 Nh7 18. Qc4 Qd7 19. e5
b5 {was hugely unclear in M.Mchedlishvili-Z.Efimenko, Dresden Olympiad 2008,
