wins, but this was unnecessary, given this was a rapid game.}) 31. Re3 $2 {
EXERCISE: What should Black do now?} (31. Ne2 $1 Bxe4 32. Nxd4 exd4 33. b4 Re5
{was White's only try, but Black has regained the pawn and is better.}) 31...
Bxe4 $1 {ANSWER: There is a tactic in the air, based on the idea of ...Nf3+
forking king and queen.} 32. Qf2 (32. Bxe4 Qxe4 33. Qd3 {, and now} ({or} 33.
Rxe4 Nf3+ 34. Kg2 Nxd2 {forks both rooks}) 33... Qxg4+ {mops up the kingside
pawns.}) 32... Bc6 33. h4 Nf3+ 34. Rxf3 (34. Kf1 Nxh4 {wins another clear pawn.
}) 34... Bxf3 35. hxg5 fxg5 36. Qe3 e4 37. Bf1 Qe7 38. b4 Qe5 39. b5 $2 (39.
Ne2 {resisted just a bit longer.}) 39... Qg3+ 0-1

